No fewer than 350 constituents of Pengana Constituency of Plateau State have benefited from the empowerment scheme of the Speaker of the Plateau State House of Assembly, Yakubu Sanda. This was revealed by the Speaker during the distribution of the empowerment items at Government Secondary School Zabolo in Bassa Local Government Area of the state. The beneficiaries, who expressed their gratitude to the Speaker, promised to make judicious use of the items and prayed to God to bestow His wisdom on him. Others who spoke separately during goodwill messages said the Speaker has not disappointed his constituents, even as they assured him of their continued support for him.   Idoma poised to produce Benue governor next year     Proposed airline service shutdown disheartening –…     Niger saves N200m from ghost pensioners – Sani-Bello   The empowerment programme, which was put together by the Speaker in collaboration with the Plateau State Micro-Finance Agency (PLASMIDA) saw over 350 beneficiaries receiving N20, 000 each. Apart from the cash support, the Speaker also distributed 10 motorcycles to some of the constituents. Presenting the items, Sanda said the gesture was in continuation of his previous empowerment programmes which were aimed at reducing poverty in Pengana Constituency. Sanda, who reaffirmed his commitment to providing purposeful leadership, urged his constituents to use their diversity as a source of unity and peaceful co-existence. The Speaker said his empowerment programme will be sustained and expanded to accommodate more beneficiaries in Pengana Constituency.